answerText: South Island [10] South Island is the less populous of the two major islands of this nation. North Island, on the other hand, is home to its capital of Wellington.

question: Question: Cook Strait lies to this island's north, while Stewart Island lies to its south across the Foveaux Strait. For 10 points each: [10] Name this home of the Southern Alps, the largest island of a certain nation, whose cities include Dunedin and Invercargill.
